{
  "_format": "req-v3",
  "_instructions": [
    "DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE BY HAND.",
    "",
    "This file is the source of truth for a managed requirements project. It is",
    "git-diffable so humans can review changes in pull requests, but every",
    "mutation must go through the `req` CLI so that best-practice validation",
    "runs (atomic statements, modal verbs, acceptance criteria, no weasel words,",
    "no broken links, etc.).",
    "",
    "Integrity: the `_integrity` field is a SHA-256 of the canonical payload.",
    "If you edit this file directly the hash will no longer match and the CLI",
    "will refuse to read it. To recover after an intentional manual edit:",
    "  req repair --confirm-direct-edit",
    "",
    "Common commands:",
    "  req init -n <name>                         create a new project",
    "  req add                                    interactive add (recommended)",
    "  req list [--status ...] [--kind ...]       table of requirements",
    "  req show REQ-0001                          full detail for one",
    "  req update REQ-0001 --status approved --reason \"team review\"",
    "  req link REQ-0002 REQ-0001 -k parent       hierarchy / traceability",
    "  req validate                               run rules across the project",
    "  req export -f markdown -o reqs.md          publish",
    "  req tui                                    interactive terminal browser",
    "  req help <section>                         structured help; try: overview,",
    "                                             concepts, best-practice, workflow,",
    "                                             file-format, agents, export",
    "",
    "Agents: never edit this file. Drive `req` with subcommands, or use `req mcp`",
    "(when available) to manage requirements through the JSON-RPC interface."
  ],
  "_integrity": "sha256:dcb326bb7d5f3af34b2c7abdde052d2cad5038a0c00a0fd658ef5c4ebb4f4072",
  "_purpose": "req is git-tracked spec-memory: a CLI that manages requirements — and an illustrative IEC 61508 safety case — across LLM-agent and human sessions. RESEARCH/EXPERIMENTAL: NOT qualified for use in real safety applications; the functional-safety features are a dogfood example, not safety assurance. This project treats req own verification integrity (HAZ-0002) as a SIL3 obligation — an illustrative indirect tool-confidence allocation, not a substantiated safety claim.",
  "_schema_rev": 1,
  "_warning": "DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE BY HAND. Managed by the `req` CLI.",
  "created": "2026-05-17T06:44:00.246918900Z",
  "hazards": {
    "HAZ-0001": {
      "avoidance": "P_B",
      "consequence": "C_C",
      "created": "2026-06-12T11:47:24.451640209Z",
      "description": "ILLUSTRATIVE dogfood example, not a literal E/E/PE safety function. req is a development tool, so 'req corrupting or mis-reporting a safety requirement' is a TOOL-CONFIDENCE concern (IEC 61508-3 §7.4.4), not an operational hazard with its own SIL. The C/F/P/W parameters are illustrative — chosen to exercise the workflow end to end — and are NOT a substantiated SIL3 claim about req's own integrity. Treat the whole HAZ-0001 chain as a worked example of the tooling, not as a safety argument.",
      "frequency": "F_B",
      "harm": "A safety requirement for the user's safety-related system is silently lost, mis-stated, or shown as Verified when it is not — so a hazard in that system goes unmitigated and a person is injured or killed downstream.",
      "history": [
        {
          "action": "created",
          "actor": "tom",
          "actor_kind": "Human",
          "at": "2026-06-12T11:47:24.451648590Z",
          "reason": null
        },
        {
          "action": "assessed",
          "actor": "tom",
          "actor_kind": "Human",
          "at": "2026-06-12T11:47:24.677157333Z",
          "reason": "Unmitigated risk: a silent spec defect is hard to catch by eye (P_B), the spec is touched continuously (F_B), and a corrupted safety requirement could contribute to several deaths in a high-integrity target (C_C)."
        },
        {
          "action": "mitigated by SF-0001",
          "actor": "tom",
          "actor_kind": "Human",
          "at": "2026-06-12T11:47:40.457543387Z",
          "reason": null
        },
        {
          "action": "updated",
          "actor": "tom",
          "actor_kind": "Human",
          "at": "2026-06-12T13:22:06.803101551Z",
          "reason": "Reframe per code review (M6): the dogfood routed a tool-confidence concern through the hardware risk graph; mark it illustrative to avoid overclaiming."
        },
        {
          "action": "updated",
          "actor": "tom",
          "actor_kind": "Human",
          "at": "2026-06-12T13:22:06.982036175Z",
          "reason": "mark dogfood as illustrative"
        }
      ],
      "id": "HAZ-0001",
      "links": [],
      "operating_context": "req is the spec-of-record for an IEC 61508 development; agents and humans mutate the spec across many sessions, with hand-edits and merges in play.",
      "probability": "W3",
      "status": "Mitigated",
      "tags": [
        "illustrative"
      ],
      "title": "[illustrative] req mis-manages a safety requirement (tool-confidence example)",
      "updated": "2026-06-12T13:22:06.982019829Z"
    },
    "HAZ-0002": {
      "avoidance": "P_B",
      "consequence": "C_C",
      "created": "2026-06-13T06:55:22.162248100Z",
      "description": "Tool-confidence hazard (IEC 61508-3 §7.4.4), generally applicable to ANY requirement, not safety-specific. The one failure mode req genuinely owns: the tool can present unverified state as trustworthy. req is a T3 offline support tool for safety work, so this is an INDIRECT safety contribution — we hold req verification-integrity controls to SIL3, the rigour of the highest safety case it is intended to support, rather than claiming req itself reduces physical risk. The C/F/P/W below are a deliberate SIL3 policy allocation, not a substantiated direct-harm assessment; actual operational severity is set by the using application. OBSERVED 2026-06-13: a stale secondary agent rubber-stamped 129 ordinary non-safety requirements to genuine-Verified with shallow or pasted-garbage dossiers, detected via the provenance report (REQ-0142) and reverted to ungated.",
      "frequency": "F_B",
      "harm": "A requirement is shown as Verified when its validation dossier was fabricated, shallow, or rubber-stamped — analysis and testing recorded as pass with no genuine basis. A stakeholder, or a downstream safety case, then trusts a spec state with no real verification behind it, and an unmet obligation ships as done.",
      "history": [
        {
          "action": "created",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "actor_kind": "Unknown",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:55:22.162255100Z",
          "reason": null
        },
        {
          "action": "updated",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "actor_kind": "Unknown",
          "at": "2026-06-13T07:01:13.522998500Z",
          "reason": "Adopt indirect-contribution SIL3 policy and build the mitigating SF/SR chain"
        },
        {
          "action": "assessed",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "actor_kind": "Unknown",
          "at": "2026-06-13T07:01:13.701791200Z",
          "reason": "Indirect safety contribution (IEC 61508-3 §7.4.4 tool confidence): req held to SIL3, the rigour of the highest safety case it is intended to support, for its verification-integrity controls. C/F/P/W are a SIL3 policy allocation, not a substantiated direct-harm claim."
        },
        {
          "action": "mitigated by SF-0004",
          "actor": "Tom",
          "actor_kind": "Unknown",
          "at": "2026-06-13T07:01:13.869740300Z",
          "reason": null
        }
      ],
      "id": "HAZ-0002",
      "links": [],
      "operating_context": "req is the spec-of-record across many sessions; humans, agents, and stale or secondary toolchains can all record validation dossiers, and no tool can prove an actor actually performed the analysis or testing it claims.",
      "probability": "W3",
      "status": "Mitigated",
      "tags": [
        "illustrative"
      ],
      "title": "[illustrative] req presents a requirement as Verified on a non-genuine validation dossier",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:01:13.869702700Z"
    }
  },
