          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:07:09.233763400Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "Criterion: Linking A parent B then B parent A fails with a cycle error. Implementation: creates_cycle() in src/commands/link.rs:88-115 walks same-kind links from target and returns true if it reaches from. The cycle check is applied at link.rs:27 for Parent (and DependsOn, Refines, Verifies) before any mutation. A REQ-A parent REQ-B then REQ-B parent REQ-A attempt will: first link succeeds (no prior links), second call finds chain REQ-A->REQ-B->...->REQ-A and returns Err. The criterion is fully met."
