      "title": "Agents must never read or write the file directly",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:51:01.704824300Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:06:52.237995300Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "src/storage.rs save() (lines 124-173): writes payload to a tmp file at path.with_extension('req.tmp') via fs::write (line 170), then renames atomically via fs::rename (line 171). save_directory() (lines 377-449) applies the same pattern per-requirement file (line 388 tmp, line 389 rename) and for the index (lines 445-447). A crash between write and rename leaves a .req.tmp that does not replace the canonical file — the original is never partially overwritten. The single acceptance criterion (temp-and-rename so a mid-write crash cannot corrupt) is fully met."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T06:09:29.503826200Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
