          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — The acceptance criterion is met: storage.rs lines 168-171 write every save to a .req.tmp temp file and atomically rename it over the destination; all save paths (single-file and directory variants) use this pattern. The OS-level atomic rename guarantees either the old or new file exists after a crash, never a partial write. Confirmed by the passing req_0019_save_is_atomic test evidence at commit 7107cab23.",
