          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "Criterion 1 (signature=good reported for signed commits): src/commands/audit.rs:38 uses git log format '%G?/%GS/%s'; explain_sig() at lines 191-204 maps 'G' to 'good'. Criterion 2 (unsigned commits reported as no-signature): explain_sig maps 'N' and empty string to 'no-signature'; lines 139-141 count those entries for the summary counter. Criterion 3 (--json emits per-commit records including SHA and ISO date): the Entry struct at lines 11-18 includes commit SHA and date fields from %H/%aI; lines 134-136 serialize entries as JSON in non-gate mode. All three criteria are met."
        },
