    "REQ-0039": {
      "acceptance": [
        "Every error path under --json prints a single JSON object with fields code, message and hint to stdout (the conventional channel for tool-readable data)",
        "Codes are stable word-based identifiers of the form REQ-E-<NAME> (e.g. REQ-E-NOT-FOUND, REQ-E-INTEGRITY) and are documented in req help errors",
        "Validator failures under req validate --json return an array of objects with req_id, field, rule and severity",
        "Integrity hash mismatch returns code REQ-E-INTEGRITY with a hint naming req repair --confirm-direct-edit"
      ],
