      "title": "Serialize concurrent writes with an advisory file lock",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:51:01.705083400Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:07:17.732435600Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "Criterion 1 (two concurrent adds both succeed with distinct IDs): storage.rs acquire_lock serializes load-modify-save so both writes land with unique IDs. Criterion 2 (lock released when process is killed): LockGuard uses fs2 OS advisory lock; OS releases it on process exit automatically — no stale sidecar lock can block. Criterion 3 (bounded timeout with clear error): LOCK_TIMEOUT_SECS=30 at storage.rs line 308; acquire_lock loop emits named error on timeout."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T06:11:27.772269300Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
