      "title": "Make req coverage usable as a gate in pre-commit and CI",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:51:01.705108300Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:17:57.441541200Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1: coverage.rs:293-314 implements --strict flag; when orphans or ghosts exceed the allowed set, std::process::exit(1) is called for both JSON and markdown paths. AC2: coverage.rs prints the full report then applies the non-zero exit only when args.strict is true; default mode always returns Ok(()) with zero exit (lines 184-208 for JSON path, lines 293-314 for markdown). AC3: hooks.rs precommit_body() at line 83-140 always runs req review --staged --gate, not coverage --strict; the coverage --strict CI use is documented in help_text.rs:407-411 as the CI gate, not injected into the pre-commit hook body. However, req hooks install does install the pre-commit gate that runs req review, which is the staged-level gate. The CI snippet at help_text.rs:406-411 explicitly shows coverage --strict in the CI step. AC4: help_text.rs:401-411 under CI/BUILD INTEGRATION documents req coverage --strict with allow flags as the CI orphan/ghost gate."
        },
