      "title": "Apply many mutations atomically via req batch",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:51:01.705116800Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:10:55.557541200Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 (single write, N history entries): batch.rs applies all mutations in memory then calls storage::save once (line 112 onwards); each mutation appends its own history entry before the single write. AC2 (rollback on failure): batch.rs stages all changes in a cloned project map and only proceeds to save when all mutations validate; any error returns early leaving the original file untouched. AC3 (supported kinds: add/update/link/delete): the Mutation enum in batch.rs (lines 26-106) defines Add, Update, Delete, Link, and Verify variants. AC4 (per-mutation reason, top-level default): each Mutation variant carries an optional reason field; the BatchDoc struct (line 19-23) carries a top-level reason used as fallback. All four criteria are met."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T06:14:28.534032200Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
