        "plan": "Read batch.rs and tests/slice_c.rs to verify all four acceptance criteria: single-write atomic application, full rollback on validation failure, supported mutation kinds (add/update/link/delete), and per-mutation reason support. Cite automated test records at HEAD 7107cab.",
        "statement": "All four acceptance criteria are met: batch.rs implements a single file write per batch with N history entries; any validation failure leaves project.req byte-identical via early return before save; Add/Update/Link/Delete mutation kinds are all present in the Mutation enum; each mutation carries an optional reason with a top-level BatchDoc default. Five automated tests pass at HEAD 7107cab.",
