      "title": "Summarize spec changes between git refs via req diff",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:53:35.164597Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T07:53:34.776438900Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 (one entry per changed req, field-level transitions, reason from history): diff.rs lines 69-79 iterate intersection of base/head IDs, call compare() to extract field transitions, and attach the latest history reason via latest_history_reason(). AC2 (added/removed in distinct sections): diff.rs lines 62-67 build separate added and removed vectors. AC3 (--json mode): diff.rs emits a stable JSON object containing added, removed, and changed arrays when args.json is set. AC4 (zero exit, empty-diff message when no changes): the function checks whether all three buckets are empty and prints a clear no-changes message then returns Ok(()). All four criteria are met."
        },
