      "title": "Hide obsolete requirements from default req list output",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T07:51:01.705181300Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:12:09.596251900Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "Criterion 1 (req list omits Obsolete by default): list.rs:60 computes hide_obsolete = !args.include_obsolete && status != Some(Obsolete); line 64 filters requirements matching this flag. Criterion 2 (--include-obsolete brings them back): cli.rs ListArgs has include_obsolete bool flag (cli.rs:1172); setting it causes hide_obsolete=false. Criterion 3 (req show still renders obsolete by ID): show.rs uses storage::load_resolved and resolve_id with no status filter; obsolete requirements are returned. Criterion 4 (--status obsolete lists only obsolete): list.rs:60 sets hide_obsolete=false when status==Some(Obsolete), and line 67 filters to only that status. Three tests req_0073_obsolete_hidden_from_default_list, req_0073_include_obsolete_flag_brings_them_back, req_0073_status_obsolete_filter_still_works passed at commit 7107cab (slice_a.rs)."
        },
