          "summary": "AC1 REQ-V-0021 per distinct cycle: validate.rs:680 pushes Finding::err REQ-V-0021 for each cycle returned by find_cycles; find_cycles uses a BTreeSet<Vec<String>> so each distinct canonical cycle is stored once. AC2 dedup by canonical rotation smallest-ID first: find_cycles (validate.rs:1053-1062) rotates the cycle vector so the minimum ID is first, then inserts into BTreeSet which deduplicates by value. AC3 all four asymmetric kinds checked: validate.rs:666-672 iterates over [Parent, DependsOn, Refines, Verifies] calling find_cycles for each. AC4 MCP req_validate surfaces the same finding with rule_code: the RULES catalog at validate.rs:86-88 includes REQ-V-0021; the MCP server calls the same validate_project function so findings are identical. All four criteria satisfied."
        },
