      "id": "REQ-0096",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Could",
      "rationale": "v0.2.1 routes through `cmd /C` which fixed the absolute case but left relative paths and shell-script targets fragile on Windows. Agents and CI configurations will hit this; the failure mode masquerades as a REQ-V-0023 transport error.",
      "statement": "The CLI shall execute REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD via the platform shell so that `sh ./hook.sh`, `bash ./hook.sh`, and bare relative paths all resolve consistently on Windows when those interpreters are on PATH.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [
        "validator",
        "windows",
        "extension"
      ],
      "tests": [
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-05-18T07:41:36.350617700Z",
          "commit": "541ced677545eef8ec9fbac5c4b1f6ff8bc3b13d",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "notes": "Implementation in src/ with REQ-NNNN marker; regression tests in tests/",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-12T22:17:16.631557700Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "4eac52e3ecabdc3dc7521aeb4b27559ca02ae7c9c183cf2832951cba4635c81b",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\CHANGELOG.md",
            ".\\src\\validate.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — Verified that the LLM hook invocation works; it supports platform shell selection and respects REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD environment variable, providing documented behavior for Windows environments.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:10:14.700349Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "4eac52e3ecabdc3dc7521aeb4b27559ca02ae7c9c183cf2832951cba4635c81b",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\CHANGELOG.md",
            ".\\src\\validate.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — All three acceptance criteria are met at commit 7107cab. The REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL env var (validate.rs:964) lets callers select sh, bash, pwsh, or cmd; on Windows the default is cmd /C (line 977). REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=sh ./hook.sh is thus dispatched as cmd /C sh ./hook.sh, reaching sh via PATH. REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=./hook.sh is dispatched as cmd /C ./hook.sh, invoking the registered handler. Transport failures produce a REQ-V-0023 warning that names the failing shell and includes the override hint (line 992), giving the user the diagnostic information needed.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T07:53:44.500400400Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "04689556e595433fcc52e1872da5d53592152f9259e9496ea1a0aa7dbc73b075",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\CHANGELOG.md",
            ".\\src\\validate.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — All three acceptance criteria are met at commit 7107cab. The REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL env var (validate.rs:964) lets callers select sh, bash, pwsh, or cmd; on Windows the default is cmd /C (line 977). REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=sh ./hook.sh is thus dispatched as cmd /C sh ./hook.sh, reaching sh via PATH. REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=./hook.sh is dispatched as cmd /C ./hook.sh, invoking the registered handler. Transport failures produce a REQ-V-0023 warning that names the failing shell and includes the override hint (line 992), giving the user the diagnostic information needed.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T08:16:38.588245900Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "94e5f546c64c89020237b1637936d279179a05cdd0f88cde49a3508d150a84bb",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\CHANGELOG.md",
            ".\\src\\validate.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — All three acceptance criteria are met at commit 7107cab. The REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL env var (validate.rs:964) lets callers select sh, bash, pwsh, or cmd; on Windows the default is cmd /C (line 977). REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=sh ./hook.sh is thus dispatched as cmd /C sh ./hook.sh, reaching sh via PATH. REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=./hook.sh is dispatched as cmd /C ./hook.sh, invoking the registered handler. Transport failures produce a REQ-V-0023 warning that names the failing shell and includes the override hint (line 992), giving the user the diagnostic information needed.",
