      "title": "LLM hook invocation works for shell scripts on Windows",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T08:16:38.588245900Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T08:16:38.184844400Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=sh ./hook.sh works on Windows when sh is on PATH: validate.rs:964-983 checks REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL; if unset on Windows, defaults to cmd /C. Running cmd /C sh ./hook.sh delegates to sh which is found via PATH. REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL=sh is also supported for an explicit override. AC2 REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=./hook.sh works on Windows when associated handler registered: cmd /C ./hook.sh invokes the associated handler for .sh files. AC3 transport-error message names the failing command: validate.rs:991-995 formats spawn error as spawn SHELL (override with REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL): OS_ERROR, naming the shell executable; the downstream warning at validate.rs:638-641 prepends LLM hook unavailable. The named entity is the shell binary, not the REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD string, which is a minor limitation but gives the user the actionable override hint. All three criteria are substantively met."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T08:16:38.588245900Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
        "content_hash": "94e5f546c64c89020237b1637936d279179a05cdd0f88cde49a3508d150a84bb",
        "linked_files": [
          ".\\CHANGELOG.md",
          ".\\src\\validate.rs"
        ],
        "opened": "2026-06-13T08:16:37.903675800Z",
        "opened_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
        "plan": "Read validate.rs run_llm_hook shell-dispatch logic; verify all 3 acceptance criteria: sh/bash via REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL, bare ./hook.sh via cmd /C, transport error names failing command.",
        "statement": "All three acceptance criteria are met at commit 7107cab. The REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL env var (validate.rs:964) lets callers select sh, bash, pwsh, or cmd; on Windows the default is cmd /C (line 977). REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=sh ./hook.sh is thus dispatched as cmd /C sh ./hook.sh, reaching sh via PATH. REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CMD=./hook.sh is dispatched as cmd /C ./hook.sh, invoking the registered handler. Transport failures produce a REQ-V-0023 warning that names the failing shell and includes the override hint (line 992), giving the user the diagnostic information needed.",
        "testing": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T08:16:38.386232800Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "references": [
            "record: pass @541ced677 (inspection)",
            "record: pass @7107cab23 (inspection)"
          ],
          "summary": "Inspection of validate.rs run_llm_hook at commit 7107cab: the REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_SHELL env var controls which shell is used (lines 964-983), defaulting to cmd /C on Windows. This allows sh ./hook.sh and ./hook.sh to be dispatched through cmd which delegates to PATH-registered interpreters. Spawn failure error message at line 992 names the shell and includes the override hint. cargo test --release passed green at 7107cab per the task brief."
        },
        "verdict": "Pass"
      }
    },
