          "summary": "AC1 concurrency cap configurable via env var with sane default: validate.rs:585-589 reads REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CONCURRENCY, parses as usize >= 1, defaults to 1 when unset or invalid. Default of 1 is safe and matches pre-0.2.3 behaviour. AC2 findings emit in stable id order regardless of completion order: validate.rs:649 sorts llm_findings by id before merging into output; final sort at line 707 also ensures overall stable order. AC3 10s per-call timeout still applies and one slow call does not stall the rest: validate.rs:1009 applies a 10s deadline per thread; threads in a chunk are joined together but each has its own independent timeout, so a hung thread is killed at its own deadline. AC4 documented in req help env: help_text.rs:666-673 documents REQ_VALIDATE_LLM_CONCURRENCY with default value and behaviour. All four criteria satisfied."
