          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — Verified post-commit hook implementation provides a calm summary of changes via # req review: origin/main..HEAD\n\n**Status:** FAIL — 5 req(s) added / 133 changed / 0 removed; validate 1 error(s), 0 warning(s); coverage 0 ghost(s), 0 markerless source file(s); 3 stale, 0 drifted record(s).\n\n## Added requirements\n\n- **REQ-0139** — Staged validation dossier gates promotion to Verified\n- **REQ-0140** — Preserve unknown schema fields across load and save\n- **REQ-0141** — Refuse to overwrite a project file written by a newer schema revision\n- **REQ-0142** — Report true verification provenance for every requirement\n- **REQ-0143** — Forbid validation exemptions for safety requirements\n\n## Changed requirements\n\n- **REQ-0001** — Manage requirements through a single CLI binary (verified)\n- **REQ-0002** — Store requirements in a git-diffable file (verified)\n- **REQ-0003** — Detect direct edits via integrity hash (verified)\n- **REQ-0004** — Embed managed-file warning and CLI directions in the file (verified)\n- **REQ-0005** — Provide req repair to re-sign after intentional edits (verified)\n- **REQ-0006** — Enforce normative-modal-verb rule on statements (verified)\n- **REQ-0007** — Warn on weasel words in statements (verified)\n- **REQ-0008** — Require acceptance criteria for functional requirements (verified)\n- **REQ-0009** — Prevent illegal status transitions without acceptance criteria (verified)\n- **REQ-0010** — Allocate stable sequential requirement IDs (verified)\n- **REQ-0011** — Maintain append-only history per requirement (verified)\n- **REQ-0012** — Soft-delete by default to preserve traceability (verified)\n- **REQ-0013** — Reject parent links that create cycles (verified)\n- **REQ-0014** — Export to multiple human-facing formats (verified)\n- **REQ-0015** — Provide an interactive TUI for humans (verified)\n- **REQ-0016** — Provide a local web server for humans (verified)\n- **REQ-0017** — Expose an