ator findings with stable rule codes (verified)\n- **REQ-0047** — Generate .mcp.json bootstrap for MCP-capable agent clients (verified)\n- **REQ-0048** — Tools expose first-class agent guidance in descriptions (verified)\n- **REQ-0049** — Record test runs against requirements with git commit SHA (verified)\n- **REQ-0050** — Surface test records and commit drift in req show (verified)\n- **REQ-0051** — Verify allocate_id is post-validation (verified)\n- **REQ-0052** — Verify validator-reject path preserves IDs (verified)\n- **REQ-0054** — Project-level implementation status summary (verified)\n- **REQ-0055** — Drive cargo test and attach per-requirement test records (verified)\n- **REQ-0056** — Verified status backed by automated or manual evidence (verified)\n- **REQ-0059** — Publish prebuilt binaries on tagged releases (verified)\n- **REQ-0060** — Publish the crate to crates.io as req-cli (verified)\n- **REQ-0061** — Distribute under the MIT license (verified)\n- **REQ-0062** — Serialize concurrent writes with an advisory file lock (verified)\n- **REQ-0063** — Surface content drift beyond commit drift in staleness reports (verified)\n- **REQ-0064** — Provide req doctor to audit local repo setup (verified)\n- **REQ-0065** — Make req coverage usable as a gate in pre-commit and CI (verified)\n- **REQ-0066** — Apply many mutations atomically via req batch (verified)\n- **REQ-0067** — Import existing requirements from external sources (verified)\n- **REQ-0068** — Migrate project.req across format versions via req migrate (verified)\n- **REQ-0069** — Summarize spec changes between git refs via req diff (verified)\n- **REQ-0070** — Distinguish implementation and test markers in coverage (verified)\n- **REQ-0071** — Protect project.req from formatter and line-ending corruption (verified)\n- **REQ-0072** — Accept a JSON document as structured input for req add (verified)\n- **REQ-0073** — Hide obsolete requirements from default req list output (verified)\n- **REQ-0074** — D