      "title": "Validator strips priority labels before the modal-verb check",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T08:16:49.370545800Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T08:16:48.964050600Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 Must-priority Verified requirements does not trip REQ-V-0010: PRIORITY_LABEL_RE at validate.rs:183 matches Must-priority and strips it; strip_non_prose at line 189 applies it before MODAL_RE.find_iter, so Must is not counted as a modal verb. AC2 shall X and must Y still trips REQ-V-0010: without -priority suffix, must is not stripped, so MODAL_RE counts two modals (shall and must) and modal_hits > 1 triggers the compound warning at validate.rs:309. AC3 strips only when followed by -priority or -priorities: regex at line 184 requires the -priorit(y|ies) suffix; bare Must as a modal is not affected. AC4 Should/Could/Wont follow same rule for symmetry: PRIORITY_LABEL_RE includes all four labels (must|should|could|wont) at line 183. All four criteria satisfied."
        },
