      "id": "REQ-0118",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Must",
      "rationale": "Confirmed during 0.4.0-rc.1 E2E testing on req import. Running the command several times in succession with the dry-run flag produced duplicate REQ-ID batches inside project.req. Dry-run is the user contract for 'show me what would happen without changing anything'; violating it silently corrupts the spec. Root cause is likely a code path that runs parse + validate + allocate and forgets to short-circuit before save when the dry-run flag is set.",
      "statement": "The CLI shall complete every dry-run invocation without writing to project.req, so successive read-only calls produce identical reports and never duplicate REQ-IDs into the file.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [
        "bugfix",
        "import"
      ],
      "tests": [
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-05-20T11:51:14.014202600Z",
          "commit": "9064a2fe1df18c71c537952af2fff2435be231f0",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "notes": "E2E verified in 0.4.0-rc.1: md5sum of project.req identical before and after req import --dry-run. Not reproducible.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-12T23:09:36.527269200Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "e0d26948e551698612515a757e05299e552bd3c907f4d308c2d098a25a827f31",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\src\\commands\\import.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — Verified that all mutation commands respect the --dry-run flag and do not modify state or files.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        },
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:15:17.836785Z",
          "commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
          "content_hash": "e0d26948e551698612515a757e05299e552bd3c907f4d308c2d098a25a827f31",
          "kind": "Inspection",
          "linked_files": [
            ".\\src\\commands\\import.rs"
          ],
          "notes": "validation dossier concluded — Both acceptance criteria are met: import.rs gates both allocate_id and storage::save behind !args.dry_run, so consecutive dry-run calls produce zero mutations; the existing test req_0067_import_dry_run_does_not_write in tests/slice_c.rs asserts byte-identical file state before and after a dry-run import invocation at HEAD 7107cab.",
          "outcome": "Pass"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Dry-run flags must never persist mutations",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T06:15:17.836785Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T06:12:08.936190700Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 (two consecutive dry-run invocations leave project.req byte-identical): import.rs lines 88-96 skip the allocate+insert step when args.dry_run is set; line 99 gates the save() call behind !args.dry_run, so no mutation reaches disk on any dry-run invocation regardless of how many times the command is called. AC2 (regression test): tests/slice_c.rs lines 109-132 (req_0067_import_dry_run_does_not_write) ingests a markdown doc with --dry-run, reads the file before and after, and asserts byte identity. Both criteria are met."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T06:15:17.836785Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
        "content_hash": "e0d26948e551698612515a757e05299e552bd3c907f4d308c2d098a25a827f31",
        "linked_files": [
