      "id": "REQ-0130",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Should",
      "rationale": "A Verified requirement with a failing latest test record is the spec asserting a falsehood about the world — it claims the behaviour works, while the most recent evidence says it does not. Surfacing this in `req validate` puts the signal in CI logs, pre-commit output, and MCP responses without breaking active development (which often involves a known-failing record while a fix is in flight). The hard block stays in `req review --gate --no-defects` (REQ-0126); this requirement is the soft, ever-present signal. Distinct from REQ-0125 because that adds the count to status/brief/lint; this adds it to validate's per-requirement findings stream where every consumer of validate already pays attention.",
      "statement": "The validator shall emit a REQ-V-0024 warning on any requirement whose status is Verified and whose latest test record has a Fail outcome, so the structural contradiction surfaces in every `req validate` call without flipping the exit code.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [
        "validator",
        "polish"
      ],
      "tests": [
