      "title": "Validator warns on Verified status with failing latest test record",
      "updated": "2026-06-13T08:16:55.835913400Z",
      "validation": {
        "actor": "Tom",
        "analysis": {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-13T08:16:55.422426700Z",
          "outcome": "Pass",
          "summary": "AC1 Verified with latest=Fail produces REQ-V-0024 warning: validate.rs:537 gates on Status::Verified, then checks r.tests.last() for Fail outcome and pushes Finding::warn REQ-V-0024 at line 540. AC2 Verified with latest=Pass produces no finding: the if let at line 538 checks latest.outcome for Fail; Pass does not match so no warning is pushed. AC3 Implemented or earlier with latest=Fail produces no REQ-V-0024: the outer gate at line 537 is Status::Verified only; Implemented does not match. AC4 warning does not flip req validate exit code: Finding::warn does not increment the error count; errors_only() at validate.rs:1081 filters by f.error which is false for warnings; exit code is driven by error count alone. All four criteria satisfied."
        },
        "concluded": "2026-06-13T08:16:55.835913400Z",
        "concluded_commit": "7107cab238bf327eab0eb41a18956905b38e8d93",
