      "id": "REQ-0131",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Should",
      "rationale": "Per-commit gate output currently reprints every project-wide compound-statement warning, including ones on requirements the author never touched. That desensitises the reader: by commit five they stop reading, burying the one real finding inside the noise. Full-project error enforcement is preserved by the dedicated req validate run on staged .req files and by CI, so scoping the review section loses no guarantee.",
      "statement": "req review shall provide a --new mode that scopes its validator findings to requirements added or changed in the compared range, so the per-commit gate does not repeat warnings about requirements the commit did not touch.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [
        "review",
        "gate"
      ],
