      "id": "REQ-0133",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Could",
      "rationale": "Broad-scope files implement several requirements, and a single file-header comment listing multiple ids reads better than line-by-line markers. Today the comment-context scan credits only the first id per line, so the rest never register as referenced. Crediting all ids on a comment line makes the header convention compose.",
      "statement": "req review shall record every REQ-NNNN id present on a recognised comment line as a referenced requirement.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [
        "review",
        "coverage"
      ],
