      "id": "REQ-0140",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [],
      "priority": "Must",
      "rationale": "An older req binary (e.g. a stale MCP server) deserialises project.req, drops fields it does not model, and re-serialises without them — silently destroying newer data such as the per-requirement validation dossier. A serde flatten catch-all on each entity makes the loss impossible going forward.",
      "statement": "The storage layer shall round-trip any unrecognised field on a requirement record, the project root, or a safety entity (hazard, safety function, safety requirement) unchanged across a load followed by a save, so a binary that does not model the field does not drop it.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [],
