      "id": "REQ-0141",
      "kind": "Functional",
      "links": [
        {
          "kind": "DependsOn",
          "target": "REQ-0140"
        }
      ],
      "priority": "Must",
      "rationale": "Forward-compatible round-tripping (REQ-0140) preserves unknown fields, but a loud refusal is a second line of defence for non-additive changes: a stale binary must stop rather than rewrite. The guard reads the on-disk _schema_rev and compares it to the binary's SCHEMA_REV before any write.",
      "statement": "The storage layer shall refuse to save over a project file whose recorded schema revision is newer than the running binary understands, failing with an upgrade-the-binary error and writing nothing.",
      "status": "Verified",
      "tags": [],
      "tests": [
        {
          "actor": "Tom",
          "at": "2026-06-12T20:34:37.862422200Z",
